result.execSummary:
The defendant Erik J Garcia was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Erik J Garcia was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Erik J Garcia is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Erik J Garcia was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Erik J Garcia was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
